Principal Python Developer

Cambridge

Generous package including share options

This is a fantastic opportunity to join our client - an AIM listed Technology Company and a key player in the ‘Internet of Things’ (IoT) agenda. Established 15 years ago, they provide a communications platform for lighting, energy and other emerging applications which are critical in improving regional infrastructure. Their solutions are of particular importance in emerging markets where the technology is an enabler of ‘Smart City’ initiatives.
With proven technology, the company is now winning larger and more significant projects globally and must therefore maintain its leading delivery capability through strengthening the team. They seek a bright, enthusiastic Principal Python Developer to manage a talented team of Python development professionals.
You will:

•	Design and deliver high quality, secure, scalable, highly available enterprise systems
•	Coordinate development plan and allocate prioritised tasks in concert with Project Manager and internal stakeholders
•	Mentor Software Team Members across two development sites and continually improve agile process
•	Undertake significant hands-on software development in Python.
•	Oversee Contractors and outsourced projects

The technical essentials:

•	Minimum 5 years’ experience delivering enterprise software systems
•	Minimum 2 years’ experience as a successful agile technical lead
•	Team lead and mentoring experience
•	Skilled Python programmer
•	Significant experience with using relational and non-relational databases, and knowledge of their comparative strengths, differences and weaknesses

Also advantageous:

•	Knowledge and practice of many programming and scripting languages. e.g. Python, C, C++, JavaScript, Perl, Bash, etc.
•	Knowledgeable about common internet protocols, standards, architectures and patterns. e.g. TCP/IP, SSL/TLS/X.509, REST
•	Versed in internet technologies commonly used in construction of web application UIs. e.g. HTTP, HTML, CSS, AngularJS, AJAX, JSON
•	Experience of ISM band radio. e.g. ZigBee, IEEE 802.15.4, 6LoWPAN, WiFi, Bluetooth

It goes without saying you will be a great communicator, capable leader and able to work without close supervision – a technical degree of some sort is also necessary. This is an opportunity to play a key role in the future of this exciting company and to participate in a potentially lucrative share scheme. Please send CVs to applications@mallorypartners.com quoting MP493.


We look forward to speaking with you,


Mallory Partners.
